Test::WWW::Mechanize::Driver
============================

Write Test::WWW::Mechanize tests in YAML. This module will load the tests
make a plan and run the tests. Supports every-page tests, SKIP, TODO, and
any object supporting the Test::WWW::Mechanize interface.


DEPENDENCIES

This module requires these other modules and libraries (perls older than
5.8 may need additional non-core modules):

  - URI
  - URI::QueryParam
  - Test::WWW::Mechanize
  - YAML                     or equivalent
  - Template                 only if you use template values
  - DateTime                 only if you use template values

For a complete tree of dependencies, see:

  http://deps.cpantesters.org/?module=Test::WWW::Mechanize::Driver


INSTALLATION

To install this module type the following:

   perl Makefile.PL
   make
   make test
   make install


